Difficulties in Emoption Regulation Scale - 16 (Bjureberg et al. 2016

Scoring: 	1: Almost Never 
	        2: Sometimes 
	        3: About half the time 
	        4: Most of the time 
	        5: Almost always 
Instructions: Please indicate how often the following statements apply to you by writing the appropriate number from the scale above           

Item      
DERS1_timepoint     		I have difficulty making sense out of my feelings
DERS2_timepoint        		I am confused about how I feel
DERS3_timepoint      		When I’m upset, I have difficulty getting work done
DERS4_timepoint 	      	When I’m upset, I become out of control
DERS5_timepoint 	      	When I’m upset, I believe I will remain that way for a long time
DERS6_timepoint 	      	When I’m upset, I believe that I’ll end up feeling very depressed
DERS7_timepoint 	     	When I’m upset, I have difficulty focusing on other things
DERS8_timepoint 	      	When I’m upset, I feel ashamed with myself for feeling that way
DERS9_timepoint 	      	When I am upset, I feel out of control
DERS10_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I feel like I am weak
DERS11_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I have difficulty controlling my behaviours
DERS12_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I believe there is nothing I can do to make myself feel better
DERS13_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I become irritated with myself for feeling that way
DERS14_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I start to feel very bad about myself
DERS15_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, I have difficulty thinking about anything else
DERS16_timepoint 	    	When I’m upset, my emotions feel overwhelming

R CODE 
mydata$DERS <- (mydata$DERS1_timepoint + mydata$DERS2_timepoint + mydata$DERS3_timepoint + mydata$DERS4_timepoint + mydata$DERS5_timepoint + mydata$DERS6_timepoint + mydata$DERS7_timepoint + mydata$DERS8_timepoint + mydata$DERS9_timepoint + mydata$DERS10_timepoint + mydata$DERS11_timepoint + mydata$DERS12_timepoint + mydata$DERS13_timepoint + mydata$DERS14_timepoint + mydata$DERS15_timepoint + mydata$DERS16_timepoint)
